cell("markdown","### Step 2: Action Selection (Heuristic Minimax)\nThe Agent uses its Neural Network as the heuristic evaluation function for Minimax. Instead of searching all the way to the end of the game, it searches `depth=2`, and uses `evaluate_board` to score the resulting states!"),
cell("code","def get_neuro_move(agent, board, player, depth=2):\n    # A simplified version:\n    # Generate all legal moves.\n    # For each move, simulate it.\n    # Pass the resulting board into agent.evaluate_board().\n    # If player is 1, pick the move with the highest eval.\n    # If player is -1, pick the move with the lowest eval.\n    # YOUR CODE HERE\n    pass"),
cell("markdown","### Step 3: The Tournament Evaluation\nWrite `evaluate_generation(population)` that pits agents against each other in random pairings. \nReturn their total scores (+1 for win, 0 for tie, -2 for loss)."),
cell("code","def evaluate_generation(population):\n    scores = {agent: 0 for agent in population}\n    \n    # E.g. each agent plays 5 games against random opponents\n    # for agent in population:\n    #    for _ in range(5):\n    #        opponent = random.choice(population)\n    #        play_game(agent, opponent) \n    #        update scores based on winner\n    # YOUR CODE HERE\n    \n    return scores"),
cell("markdown","### Step 4: Evolution Loop\nLoop through `G` generations!"),
cell("code","def evolve(generations=50):\n    # 1. Init population of 15\n    population = [NeuroAgent() for _ in range(15)]\n    \n    for g in range(generations):\n        # 2. Mutate: create 15 children\n        children = []\n        for p in population:\n            child = NeuroAgent(copy_from=p)\n            child.mutate()\n            children.append(child)\n            \n        # 3. Evaluate all 30\n        full_pop = population + children\n        scores = evaluate_generation(full_pop)\n        \n        # 4. Select top 15 to survive\n        # sort full_pop by scores, keep top 15\n        # population = ...\n        \n        print(f\"Gen {g} Max Score: {max(scores.values())}\")\n        \n    return population[0] # Return the GOAT"),
cell("markdown","---\n## Phase 2 — Experimental Verification\n\n### The Ultimate Test\nTrain your population for 50 generations. Then play a game against the GOAT!\nDoes it play better than random? Did it learn to block your wins without *ever* being explicitly told the rules of the game?"),
